																								 New Delhi, Oct. 18: The government has cleared 14 foreign direct investment proposals worth Rs 1,257 crore, including those of Mauritius-based Essar Telecom Holdings Ltd and us-based Goldman Sachs Asset Management. Foreign equity worth Rs 500 crore will come from Essar Telecom and Rs 200 crore from Goldman Sachs. The government also approved a Rs 480-crore plan by Greenko Mauritius.																								 New Delhi, Oct. 18: The government has reported a 40 per cent jump in direct tax collection at Rs 1,21,950 crore till October 15 this fiscal against Rs 86,751 crore during the same period last fiscal.																								 Mumbai, Oct. 18: Swiss cement maker Holcim Ltd has postponed an open offer to buy a further 20 per cent stake in Ambuja Cements Ltd. The offer, which was scheduled to open on October 18, has been postponed till further notice.																								 New Delhi, Oct. 18: The board of approval, headed by commerce secretary g. k. Pillai, will take up 15 more proposals for special economic zones tomorrow.																								 New Delhi, Oct. 18: The power ministry proposes to float power bonds, Vidyut Vikas Patra, to raise Rs 50,000 crore to fund various projects under the 11th Five-Year Plan.
